This extra payment is administered by the executive agency responsible for the delivery of devolved social security benefits in Scotland, Social Security Scotland. To qualify, a person must already be claiming Carer’s Allowance.  Carer’s Allowance Supplement is paid twice a year. The two separate payments are each made up of £231.40. There are two Carer's Allowance Supplement eligibility dates each year - one in April and the other is in October.  For example, the first payment will be delivered in June if claimants receive Carer’s Allowance by April 12, 2022.  In this case, the second payment could be delivered in December if Carer’s Allowance recipients get paid by October 11, 2022. This means that claimants of Carer’s Allowance Supplement could receive £462.80 a year. Only residents of Scotland are eligible.  People do need to apply for Carer’s Allowance Supplement as they should be paid it automatically. DON'T MISS:   In some cases, a person can apply for the supplement if they're a resident in the EU, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway or Switzerland. Data from the Scottish Government shows that carers in Scotland received nearly £700 more than carers across the rest of the UK last year through the additional Coronavirus Carer’s Allowance Supplement payment. 82,000 eligible carers received this additional double payment in December 2021. Over 658,000 Carer’s Allowance Supplement payments have been made to 126,055 carers since this additional payment was introduced in September 2018.  Since 658,000 Carer's Allowance Supplement payments have been made since 2018, this would amount to £188million that has been paid to carers, according to data from the Scottish Government. Furthermore, the Scottish Government has confirmed that it will provide additional funding to help unpaid carers. This includes an extra £3million for local carer centres across the country and £200,000 for the Young Carers Package, a scheme which provides opportunities and days out for young carers. An additional £377,000 has been reserved to expand Family Fund support with breaks for parents and families looking after disabled children and young people.  What is happening where you live? Find out by adding your postcode or visit InYourArea £600,000 will be spent will fund initiatives for young carers who look after those with Dementia. Carer's Allowance Supplement is an extra payment for people in Scotland who get Carer's Allowance on a particular date. Carer's Allowance is a benefit for individuals who provide regular and substantial care to a disabled person. It is a taxable benefit and forms part of a person's taxable income. Carer's Allowance is set to rise by 3.1 percent to £69.70 from April 11, 2022. 